    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-08-11T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1957-08-11T22:00:00-05:00" n="503"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d503">
                <head>503. Telegram From the Counselor of the Embassy in Paraguay (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HR1" type="from">Hilton</persName>) to the <gloss type="to"
                        >Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d503fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 411.006/8–1157. Confidential; <gloss target="#t_niact1"
                        >Niact</gloss>. Repeated to Rio de Janeiro.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1957-08-11T23:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 11, 1957—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>53. Department for <persName corresp="#p_SWP1">Snow</persName> from <persName
                        corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName>; Rio de Janeiro for Doctor <persName
                        corresp="#p_HG1">Gabriel Hauge</persName> care of Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_ARB1">Anderson</persName>
                    <note n="2" xml:id="d503fn2">
                        <persName corresp="#p_HG1">Hauge</persName> and Secretary of the Treasury
                            <persName corresp="#p_ARB1">Anderson</persName> stopped in Rio de
                        Janeiro en route to the Buenos Aires Economic Conference.</note> from
                        <persName corresp="#p_RRRJ1">Rubottom</persName>. Plumbed depth tung oil
                    problem with Foreign Minister and Deputy Foreign Minister in presence four other
                    cabinet ministers and leading exporter who is American. They recognize US
                    problem but insist grave political consequences would result if <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> assumed onus for reduced exports before own
                    people.</p>
                <p>To be acceptable <gloss target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> would expect plan to contain
                    separate Paraguayan quota. Their strong feelings about being included in global
                    quota with Argentina understandable even if unrealistic. Believe <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss>’s point valid that suggested export figures
                    should have been calculated on last two years shipments instead of five since
                    contraband to Argentina largely stopped two years ago.</p>
                <p>If unilateral action our part can be further delayed until I can consult with
                        <persName corresp="#p_HG1">Hauge</persName> Buenos Aires it is conceivable
                    some agreement with Paraguay still could be reached. On basis 25,000,000 pounds
                        <pb facs="1048" n="1014" xml:id="pg_1014"/> annual imports <gloss
                        target="#t_GOP1">GOP</gloss> would insist on 15 to 20 as Paraguay’s separate
                    quota.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HR1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Hilton</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
